      "message": "Just a suggestion, We can  use 'ConsumerRecord<K, V>' to access the raw kafka message including headers. This avoids the conversion happening at line 70 in this file and also in EventPublisher at line 94(convertToKafkaHeader). We can refer 'https://docs.spring.io/spring-kafka/api/org/springframework/kafka/annotation/KafkaListener.html'\n\nIf you fell good to continue with the one you written, I am ok, but for avoiding the conversion to Map externally(line 71). we can use '@Headers Map<String, Object> at line 62 as a parameter)'",
